    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-11T04:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-11T04:30:00-05:00" n="446"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">756D.5–<gloss target="#t_MSP1"
                    >MSP</gloss>/12–1151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Indonesia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cochran</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Djakarta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-11T17:00:00+07:30"
                            >December 11, 1951—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>848. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 602.<note n="1" xml:id="d446fn1"
                        >Not here printed; the Department of State, in telegram 602 to Djakarta,
                        December 7, merely repeated the contents of telegram 2963 to Paris, November
                        16 (601.56D11/12–751). For the gist of this telegram sent to Paris, see
                        footnote 3, <ref target="#pg_730">p. 730</ref>.</note> I discussed with
                        <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> Subardjo today question US
                    providing <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> with mil equipment. Subardjo
                    said he was requesting <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> mil auths provide
                    description and quantities of items needed. He said such aid wld be sought on
                    reimbursable basis.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cochran</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
